            "type": "text",
            "text": "Short-term memory is the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list passed to every "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "client.messages.create",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " call. It is the only information the model has access to at each step \u2014 there is no background state, no persistent store, and no shared memory across calls. Everything the agent has seen, done, and discovered lives in this list, accumulated step by step, and re-sent in full on every call. Understanding how it grows, how to measure it, and when to trim or summarise it is essential for writing agents that run reliably beyond a handful of steps."
          }
        ]
      },
