      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Tool result size is the primary variable. Truncating large results before appending them to messages is more effective at extending the run length than any other strategy."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Measuring Memory State"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Log the memory state at the start of each step to catch context growth before it causes an API error:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def count_messages(messages: list[dict]) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Count messages by role and estimate token usage.\n    Useful for logging at the start of each loop step.\n    \"\"\"\n    user_turns = sum(1 for m in messages if m[\"role\"] == \"user\")\n    assistant_turns = sum(1 for m in messages if m[\"role\"] == \"assistant\")\n    # Rough token estimate: 1 token \u2248 4 characters\n    approx_tokens = sum(len(str(m)) // 4 for m in messages)\n    return {\n        \"total_messages\": len(messages),\n        \"user_turns\": user_turns,\n        \"assistant_turns\": assistant_turns,\n        \"approx_tokens\": approx_tokens,\n        \"pct_of_200k\": round(approx_tokens / 200_000 * 100, 1),\n    }\n\n\ndef log_memory_state(messages: list[dict], step: int) -> None:\n    stats = count_messages(messages)\n    print(\n        f\"Step {step}: {stats['total_messages']} messages, \"\n        f\"~{stats['approx_tokens']:,} tokens ({stats['pct_of_200k']}% of 200k)\"\n    )\n\n\n# Use in the agent loop:\n# for step in range(MAX_STEPS):\n#     log_memory_state(messages, step)\n#     response = client.messages.create(...)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Log at each step, not just at the end",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 a context overflow fails mid-run. Knowing the token count at step 15 lets you trigger trimming at step 16 before the overflow happens."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "4 characters \u2248 1 token",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 the approximation is rough but fast. For production monitoring, use the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "usage",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " field in the API response for the exact count."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set a threshold, not a hard limit",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 start trimming at 80% of the context window, not 100%. This leaves room for the next tool result."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trimming Old Tool Pairs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest strategy for managing context growth is to remove the oldest tool_use / tool_result pairs when the token count exceeds a threshold. The task prompt at "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages[0]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is always preserved:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def trim_oldest_tool_pairs(\n    messages: list[dict],\n    keep_first_n: int = 1,\n    max_tokens: int = 160_000,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Remove oldest tool_use / tool_result pairs when the context is getting full.\n    Always keeps the first keep_first_n messages (the task prompt).\n\n    Returns a new list \u2014 does not modify in place.\n    \"\"\"\n    def approx_tokens(msgs):\n        return sum(len(str(m)) // 4 for m in msgs)\n\n    result = list(messages)\n    while approx_tokens(result) > max_tokens and len(result) > keep_first_n + 2:\n        # Find the first removable pair after the protected prefix\n        for i in range(keep_first_n, len(result) - 1):\n            # A tool_use / tool_result pair: assistant then user with tool_result\n            if (\n                result[i][\"role\"] == \"assistant\"\n                and result[i + 1][\"role\"] == \"user\"\n            ):\n                result = result[:i] + result[i + 2:]\n                break\n        else:\n            break  # Nothing removable\n\n    return result\n\n\n# Trim before the context exceeds 160k tokens\nmessages = trim_oldest_tool_pairs(messages, keep_first_n=1, max_tokens=160_000)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove pairs, not individual messages",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 removing only the assistant turn without the corresponding user turn breaks the alternating-role invariant and causes an API error. Always remove both."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preserve the task prompt",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "keep_first_n=1",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " ensures "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "messages[0]",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (the original task) is never removed. Without it, the model loses track of what it is doing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Trim to 80% of the limit",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 setting "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "max_tokens=160_000",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " leaves 40k tokens of headroom for the next several steps before trimming is needed again."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summarising History"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When trimming discards too much context, summarisation preserves the essential information in fewer tokens. A compact summary replaces the trimmed messages, letting the model continue with awareness of what happened in earlier steps:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n\ndef summarise_history(\n    messages: list[dict],\n    keep_last_n: int = 4,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replace old messages with a compact summary so the model retains\n    the essence of past steps without the full token cost.\n\n    Returns a new list:\n      [original task] + [summary turn] + [last keep_last_n message pairs]\n    \"\"\"\n    if len(messages) <= keep_last_n * 2 + 1:\n        return messages  # not long enough to need summarisation\n\n    task = messages[0]\n    to_summarise = messages[1 : len(messages) - keep_last_n * 2]\n    recent = messages[len(messages) - keep_last_n * 2 :]\n\n    # Ask the model to compress the history\n    summary_response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=800,\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": (\n                \"Summarise the following agent steps into 200 words. \"\n                \"Focus on what was found, what was changed, and what remains to be done. \"\n                \"Do not repeat tool arguments or full file contents.\\n\\n\"\n                + str(to_summarise)\n            )},\n        ],\n    )\n    summary_text = summary_response.content[0].text\n\n    summary_message = {\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": f\"[Summary of earlier steps]\\n{summary_text}\",\n    }\n\n    return [task, summary_message] + recent\n"
          }
        ]
      },
